GALE WARNING: IN OPERATION
SMALL CRAFT. WARNING: IN OPERATION
2. METEOROLOGICAL SITUATION AT 0500: AN ACTIVE COLD FRONT WITH WAVES
IS MOVING SOUTHEASTWARDS ACROSS IRELAND PRECEDED BY A VERY STRONG SOUTH
TO SOUTHWESTERLY AIRFLOW AND FOLLOWED BY A MOSTLY MODERATE TO FRESH WEST
TO NORTHWEST AIRFLOW. A WEAK RIDGE WILL FOLLOW FROM THE WEST TODAY. A WARM
FRONT WILL MOVE NORTHWARDS ACROSS THE COUNTRY THIS EVENING AND TONIGHT FOLLOWED
BY A STRENGTHENING SOUTHERLY AIRFLOW.
3. FORECAST FOR COASTS FROM ERRIS HEAD TO MALIN HEAD TO BELFAST LOUGH:
WIND: WEST TO NORTHWEST FORCE 5 OR 6 AND GUSTY DECREASING WESTERLY FORCE
3 OR 4 BY EVENING BACKING SOUTHEASTERLY THIS EVENING AND INCREASING FORCE
5 TO 7 EARLY TONIGHT STRONGEST IN THE NORTHWEST FURTHER INCREASING SOUTHEASTERLY
FORCE 7 TO GALE FORCE 8 OVERNIGHT.
FORECAST FOR COASTS FROM BELFAST LOUGH TO CARNSORE POINT TO ROCHES POINT
AND FOR THE IRISH SEA: WIND: SOUTH TO SOUTHWEST GALE FORCE 8 TO STRONG GALE
9 AT FIRST VEERING WEST TO NORTHWEST THIS MORNING AND DECREASING FORCE 4
OR 5. FURTHER DECREASING WESTERLY OR VARIABLE FORCE 2 TO 4 THIS AFTERNOON.
WINDS WILL BACK EAST TO SOUTHEAST LATER TODAY AND EARLY TONIGHT. INCREASING
FORCE 5 OR 6 BY MIDNIGHT FURTHER INCREASING SOUTH TO SOUTHEAST FORCE 6 OR
7 OVERNIGHT.
FORECAST FOR COASTS FROM ROCHES POINT TO LOOP HEAD TO ERRIS HEAD:
WIND: WEST TO NORTHWEST. FORCE 4 OR 5. DECREASING WESTERLY OR VARIABLE
FORCE 2 TO 4 TODAY. WINDS WILL BACK EAST TO SOUTHEAST LATER TODAY INCREASING
FORCE 5 TO 7 THIS EVENING VEERING SOUTHERLY FOREE 6 OR 7 TONIGHT AND POSSIBLY
REACHING GALE FORCE 8 AT TIMES IN THE WEST.
WEATHER FOR ALL SEA AREAS: RAIN CLEARING SOUTHEASTWARDS THIS MORNING WITH
JUST ISOLATED SHOWERS FOLLOWING. MORE RAIN WILL EXTEND FROM THE SOUTHWEST
AND SOUTH THIS EVENING AND TONIGHT WITH A RISK OF FOG.
VISIBILITY FOR ALL SEA AREAS: BECOMING MOSTLY GOOD TODAY BUT MODERATE
TO POOR THIS EVENING AND TONIGHT.
3A. WARNING OF HEAVY SWELL: ON SOUTHERN WESTERN AND NORTHWESTERN COASTS.
4. OUTLOOK FOR A FURTHER 24 HOURS UNTIL 0600 TUESDAY 08 DECEMBER 2015 SOUTHERLY
GALES OR STRONG GALES POSSIBLY REACHING STORM FORCE AT TIMES ON ATLANTIC
COASTS ON MONDAY DECREASING STRONG TO GALE FORCE SOUTHERLY MONDAY NIGHT.
